 trainer!</span><hr size=1> I was grouped with an ogre and a halfling yesterday.  We were having fun and then the ogre had to camp.  Without our tank there wasn't much point in me and the halfling (I'm a human wizard) continuing, so he took off.  Just as the halfling was out of sight and the Ogre disappared, a lion started attacking me from the side.  I turned to see him and then tried rooting him then backed up.  There happened to be an elf medding right behind me as I backed up, so when my root wore off (quickly), the lion started attacking him.  I figured we could both fend him off, but the elf just ran away with the lion chasing him.  They were both faster than me so I couldn't keep up.  After a minute I gated home.  The elf was there and he reamed me out saying I was a trianer and that I purposely led the lion to him to kill him.  It all happened so fast.  I didn't even know he was there.  I tried to explain to him but he just said, &quot;sure&quot; and camped.  I'm really upset at this because most people take me at my word, but this guy didn't.  Sigh...  Why do people have to assume the worst?<br>
